    專任教師    










蕭新煌
回上一頁


Professor






學歷：美國紐約州立大學（水牛城）社會學博士        
              
        
        



研究室：        
                
        



電話：+886 (0)2-2652-5068        
        
        
        


E-mail：michael@gate.sinica.edu.tw



個人網頁： http://www.ios.sinica.edu.tw/fellow/hsinhuangmichaelhsiao/






研究領域發展社會學、環境社會學、東亞與東南亞中產階級、社會運動、民間公民社會與亞洲新民主、非營利組織與第三部門研究、台灣與東南亞客家研究               
        
            
    
    
    
    



研究興趣




學術發表近五年學術著作

期刊論文

●蕭新煌、許耿銘，2015，〈探析都市氣候風險的社會指標：回顧與芻議〉。《都市與計劃》42(1): 59-86。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Alan Hao Yang, 2014,“Introduction to the Special Issues-Contending Confucius Institutes in Southeast Asia ” Issues & Studies, 50(4), 1-10.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, 2013, “Ethnic Movements, NGOs, and Their Impacts on Ethnic Policies in Today`s Taiwan”Asia Pacific World, 4(1), 5-14.

●蕭新煌、楊昊，2013，〈東亞的柔性權力政治：中國與日本如何競逐區域領導權？〉。《國際關係研究月刊》9: 98-105。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2013. “Precarious Work in Taiwan: A Profile” American Behavioral Scientist, 57(3):373-389. 

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2013. “The Triple Turn of Taiwanese Sociology” Global Dialogue, 3(2):19-20.

●Alan Hao Yang and Hsin-Hung Michael Hsiao. 2012. “Confucius Institutes and the Question of China`s Soft Power Diplomacy” China Brief, 12(13), 10-13.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2012. “Taïwan: acquis, dilemmes et défis des mouvements sociaux”, État des résistances dans le Sud Asie, Vol. 19-2012/4.

●楊昊、蕭新煌、趙晧嵎，2012，〈中國知識社群如何重構「柔性權力」理論？回顧與批判〉。《中國大陸研究》，55(4): 59-88。

●Timothy Ka-Ying Wong, Po-San Wan and Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2011. “The Bases of Political Trust in Six Asian Societies: Institutional and Cultural Explanations Compared”, International Political Science Review 32(2): 263-281. 

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and L. C. Russell Hsiao. 2011. “The Challenges and Prospect of Taiwan`s Democracy”, Panorama: Insights into Asian and European Affairs, No. 2, 105-115.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Po-San Wan, Timothy Ka-Ying Wong. 2010. “Globalization and Public Attitudes towards the State in the Asia-Pacific Region” Japanese Journal of Political Science, 11(1), 21-49.

●蕭新煌，2010，〈從東南亞台商經驗到東南亞港商現實：代專題導言〉。《亞太研究論壇》，47: 1-3。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2010. “Facing and Coping with the Economic Crisis in Taiwan: A Study of Public Opinion in 2009”, Vietnam Social Sciences 5(139), 35-44.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2010. “Taiwanese Contentious Politics and Controversies over Taiwan-China ECFA”, JPI PeaceNet, No. 2010-6.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2010. “The Changing Political Landscape in Taiwan: Implications of the Special Municipality Elections”, China Brief, 10(24), 5-7.

●Timothy Ka-Ying Wong, Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Po-San Wan. 2009. “Comparing Political Trust in Hong Kong and Taiwan: Levels, Determinants, and Implications” Japanese Journal of Political Science, 10(2), 147-174. 

●Khay-Thiong Lim and Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2009. “Is There a Transnational Hakka Identity?: Examining Hakka Youth Ethnic Consciousness in Malaysia”《台灣東南亞學刊》6(1): 49-80。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Alan Yang. 2009. “Soft Power Politics in the Asia-Pacific: Chinese and Japanese Quests for Regional Leadership” 《亞太研究論壇》43: 111-129。

書籍專章

●Petr Jen-Der Lue, Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Chien-Hung Lee, 2015, “Assessing Reform of the Policies on Nonstandard Workers in Taiwan”, editor(s): Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Arne L. Kalleberg and Kevin Hewison, Policy Responses to Precarious Work in Asia, pp. 105-134, Taipei: Institute of Sociology, Academia Sinica.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Arne L. Kalleberg and Kevin Hewison, 2015, “Featuring Policies on Precarious Work in Asia”, editor(s): Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Arne L. Kalleberg and Kevin Hewison, Policy Responses to Precarious Work in Asia, pp. 1-11, Taipei: Institute of Sociology, Academia Sinica.

●蕭新煌，2015，〈臺北都：首都的美麗與哀愁〉，蕭新煌編，《台灣地方環境的教訓：五都四縣的大代誌》，頁35-74，高雄：巨流。

●蕭新煌，2015，〈新北都：變臉的城鄉〉，蕭新煌編，《台灣地方環境的教訓：五都四縣的大代誌》，頁75-110，高雄：巨流。

●蕭新煌、紀駿傑、徐世榮、杜文苓、許耿銘，2015，〈總論：書寫台灣地方環境史〉，蕭新煌編，《台灣地方環境的教訓：五都四縣的大代誌》，頁1-34，高雄：巨流。

●蕭新煌，2015，〈導論:勾勒與定位台灣第三部門發展史II〉，蕭新煌編，《書寫台灣第三部門史II》，頁i-xii，高雄：巨流。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Khay-Thiong Lim, 2015, “History and Politics of National Cuisine: Malaysia and Taiwan”, editor(s): Kwang Ok Kim, Re-orienting Cuisine: East Asian Foodways in the Twenty-First Century, pp. 31-55, UK: Berghahn Books.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and L. C. Russell Hsiao. 2014. “After the Strongmen: The Beginning of Democracy in Asia?”, editor(s): Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Democracy or Alternative Political Systems in Asia: After the Strongmen, pp. 3-17, London & New York: Routledge.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2013. “Characterizing the Middle Classes in Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao and Urban China”, editor(s): Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Chinese Middle Classes: Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao and China, pp. 3-13, London and New York: Routledge.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Po-san Wan. 2013. “Comparing Socio-economic Attitudes of the Middle Classes in Taiwan and Hong Kong”, editor(s): Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Chinese Middle Classes: Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao and China, pp. 110-131, London and New York: Routledge.

●Ming-Chang Tsai, Gang-Hua Fan, Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Hong-Zen Wang. 2013. “Profiling the Middle Classes in Taiwan Today”, editor(s): Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Chinese Middle Classes: Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao and China, pp. 17-35, London & New York: Routledge.

●蕭新煌、林開忠，2013，〈自立、鄉愁與融入：越南配偶小吃店在臺灣〉，林開忠編，《滋味的流轉：遷徙與地域飲食文化的形成》，頁103-142，臺北：財團法人中華飲食文化基金會。

●蕭新煌、尹寶珊，2013，〈因應經濟危機與評估政府效能：2009年台港民意比較〉，楊文山、尹寶珊編，《面對挑戰：台灣與香港之比較》，頁179-208，臺北：中研院社會學研究所。

●範綱華、蕭新煌，2013，〈宗教信仰與主觀心理福祉：台港比較〉，楊文山、尹寶珊編，《面對挑戰：台灣與香港之比較》，頁27-60，臺北：中央研究院社會學研究所。

●鄭力軒、林宗弘、蕭新煌，2013，〈東アジアにおける福祉政策の再検討〉，園田茂人編，《リスクの中の東アジア》，頁115-137，東京：勁草書房。

●蕭新煌，2013，〈從臺灣客家經驗論東南亞客家研究的比較視野〉，林開忠編，《客居他鄉-東南亞客家族群的生活與文化》，頁18-23，苗慄：客家委員會客家文化發展中心。

●黃登興、蔡青龍、蕭新煌，2012，〈勾勒越南配偶小吃店的整體特徵〉，黃登興、蔡青龍、蕭新煌編，《台灣越南配偶的族裔經濟》，頁33-74，臺北：中央研究院亞太區域研究專題中心。

●黃登興、蔡青龍、蕭新煌、鄭冠榮，2012，〈研究越南配偶小吃店的背景與設計〉，黃登興、蔡青龍、蕭新煌編，《台灣越南配偶的族裔經濟》，頁11-31，臺北：中央研究院亞太區域研究專題中心。

●蕭新煌，2012，〈越南配偶族裔經濟在台灣：綜述〉，黃登興、蔡青龍、蕭新煌編，《台灣越南配偶的族裔經濟》，頁1-10，臺北：中央研究院亞太區域研究專題中心。

●範綱華、蕭新煌，2012，〈宗教は心の安寧に寄與しうるか？---日韓台の比較から〉，園田茂人編，《勃興する東アジアの中産階級》，頁177-206，東京：勁草書房。

●紀駿傑、蕭新煌，2012，〈臺灣東海岸的原住民與環境正義問題〉，楊祖漢、楊自平編，《綠色啟動：重探自然與人文的關係》，頁737-761，臺北：國立中央大學出版中心、遠流圖書。

●徐世榮、蕭新煌、許耿銘，2012，〈臺灣西海岸的城鄉落差與環境正義問題〉，楊祖漢、楊自平編，《綠色啟動：重探自然與人文的關係》，頁763-787，臺北：國立中央大學出版中心、遠流圖書。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2012. “Social Foundations of Political Vitality”, editor(s): Steve Tsang, The Vitality of Taiwan, pp. 37-56, UK: Palgrave Macmillan.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2012. “The First Generation Middle Class in Taiwan: Culture and Politics”, editor(s): David Blundell, Taiwan Since Martial Law: Society, Culture, Politics, Economics, pp. 243-262, USA and Taiwan: University of California, Berkeley and National Taiwan University Press.

●王家英、蕭新煌、尹寶珊，2011，〈政治信任的現狀和啟示：香港和臺灣的比較〉，蕭新煌、尹寶珊、王家英編，《解讀臺港社會意向》，頁237-265，香港：香港中文大學香港亞太研究所。

●蕭新煌，2011，〈什麼是族裔企業？臺灣客家企業家又是什麼？〉，江明修編，《客家企業家》，頁1-5，臺北：智勝文化。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2011. “One Colonialism, Two Memories: Representing Japanese Colonialism in Taiwan and South Korea”, editor(s): Gi-Wook Shin and Daniel C. Sneider, History Textbooks and the Wars in Asia: Divided Memories, pp. 173-190, London: Routledge.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2011. “Social Movements in Taiwan: A Typological Analysis”, editor(s): J. Broadbent V. Brockman, East Asian Social Movements, pp. 237-254, New York: Springer.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Khay-Thiong Lim, 2011, “The History and Politics of Malaysian and Taiwanese "National Cuisine"”, editor(s): David Y. H. Wu, Overseas March: How the Chinese Cuisine Spread?, pp. 297-334, Taipei: Foundation of Chinese Dietary Culture.

●楊昊、蕭新煌，2011，〈觀察亞太和平與安全的新因素：中國與日本的東南亞柔性權力外交〉，林正義、歐錫富編，《2009亞太和平觀察》，頁23-83，臺北：中央研究院亞太區域研究專題中心。

●蕭新煌，2010，〈我與臺灣的社會學想像〉，王宏仁、龔宜君編，《臺灣的社會學想像》，頁3-12，臺北：巨流圖書公司。

●蕭新煌，2010，〈台灣社會運動的挑戰與突破〉，蕭新煌、顧忠華編，《台灣社會運動再出發》，頁3-10，臺北：巨流圖書。

●蕭新煌與蕭良其，2010，〈馬英九政権と臺灣・日本の関係〉，西川潤、蕭新煌編，《東アジア新時代の日本と臺灣》，頁96-106，東京：明石書店。

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao and Ming-sho Ho. 2010. “Civil society and democracy-making in Taiwan: Reexamining the link”, editor(s): Yin-wah Chu, Siu-lun Wong, East Asia`s New Democracies: deepening, reversal, non-liberal alternatives, pp. 43-64, London and New York: Routledge.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2010. “Islam and the State: Teaching and the Political Reality”, editor(s): Ota Atsushi, Okamoto Masaki and Almad Suaedy, Islam in Contention: Rethinking of State and Islam in Indonesia, pp. 27-32, Jakarta, Kyoto and Taipei: Wahid Institute, CSEAS, University of Kyoto and CAPAS, Academia Sinica.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2010. “Placing China`s Middle Class in the Asia-Pacific Context”, editor(s): Cheng Li, China`s Emerging Middle Class: Beyond Economic Transformation, pp. 245-263, Washington D. C.: Brookings Institution Press.

●Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, I-Chun Kung and Hong-Zen Wang. 2010. “Taishang: A Different Kind of Ethnic Chinese Business in Southeast Asia”, editor(s): Chu Yin-Wah, Chinese Capitalisms: Historical Emergence and Political Implications, pp. 156-175, New York: Palgrave Macmillan.

●Hong-Zen Wang and Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao. 2009. “Gender, Family and State in East Asian Cross-Border Marriages”, editor(s): Hong-Zen Wang and Hsin-Huang Michael Hsiao, Cross-Border Marriages with Asian Characteristics, pp. 1-12, Taipei: Center for Asia-Pacific Area Studies, Academia Sinica.

●蕭新煌、王宏仁，2009，〈從東亞到東南亞的中產階級研究：理論與經驗〉，李春玲編，《比較視野下的中產階級形成：過程、影響以及社會經濟後果》，頁12-36，北京：社會科學文獻出版社。

●蕭新煌，2009，〈非營利部門在台灣的發展特色〉，蕭新煌、官有垣、陸宛蘋編，《非營利部門：組織與運作(第二版)》，頁35-45，臺北：巨流圖書。





